description:
This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_snare1.wav
tags: drum-kit slices cuts glitch noise soundeffect digital fx

contributors_browser: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.0) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/42.0.2311.152 Safari/537.36
description:
This is part of a sound kit i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-kit_clak02.wav
tags: cuts digital drum-kit fx glitch noise slices soundeffect

description:
This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-set_wet.wav
tags: crash liquid wet meachanical hi-tech button cyborg electro alien mutate processing robot soundesign switch clack transform click digital effect fx glitch slices cuts soundeffect noise

This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-set_wet.wav
tags: crash liquid wet meachanical hi-tech button cyborg electro alien mutate processing robot soundesign switch clack transform click digital effect fx glitch slices cuts soundeffect noise

Please rate, comment and share.

Peace.
Matt

contributors_browser: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:38.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/38.0
description:
This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
name: deconstruction-set_see this waveform.wav
tags: alien button clack click electro hi-tech mutate processing robot soundesign switch transform cyborg drop-out cuts slices digital soundeffect effect noise fx glitch

description:
This is part of a sound set i've done in 2002 during a session testing Deconstructor from Tobybear, the basic version
was a simple drum-loop, sliced and processed with pitchshifting, panning, tremolo, delay, reverb, vocoder.. and all those cool onboard fx
Tweaking here and there the original sound was completely mangled..
i saved the work in 2 folders: 'deconstruction-set' contain the longer slices (meant to be used with a sampler), 'deconstruction-kit' collects the smallest slices (to be used in a drum machine)
